1
00:00:30,385 --> 00:00:32,985
Neung!

2
00:00:33,065 --> 00:00:34,305
What are you doing?

3
00:00:34,385 --> 00:00:36,145
Please calm down.

4
00:00:41,385 --> 00:00:42,545
Song…

5
00:00:43,465 --> 00:00:45,065
I'm sorry.

6
00:00:46,185 --> 00:00:48,585
I really can't go on anymore.

7
00:00:48,665 --> 00:00:51,465
No, don't do this.

8
00:00:51,545 --> 00:00:53,345
Neung.

9
00:00:54,105 --> 00:00:55,985
Take good care of yourself.

10
00:00:56,585 --> 00:00:59,305
And don't forget to keep our promise.

11
00:01:00,265 --> 00:01:03,345
No, Neung.

12
00:01:03,425 --> 00:01:05,585
Neung, please don't.

13
00:01:05,665 --> 00:01:08,425
Neung.

14
00:01:12,585 --> 00:01:14,825
Neung, please no.

15
00:01:14,905 --> 00:01:17,585
Neung.

16
00:01:21,505 --> 00:01:22,705
Neung!

17
00:01:25,905 --> 00:01:27,025
Neung!

18
00:01:46,545 --> 00:01:48,425
I'm sorry.

19
00:01:52,665 --> 00:01:54,105
Don't leave me.

20
00:02:00,225 --> 00:02:01,505
Song.

21
00:02:13,945 --> 00:02:15,025
Song.

22
00:02:23,785 --> 00:02:25,345
Don't be sad anymore.

23
00:02:25,425 --> 00:02:27,305
You have to stay strong for our children.

24
00:02:29,705 --> 00:02:30,865
This is Ruean.

25
00:02:31,505 --> 00:02:32,905
And this is Rai.

26
00:02:34,345 --> 00:02:35,745
They're our twins.

27
00:02:35,825 --> 00:02:36,865
What?

28
00:02:38,425 --> 00:02:40,745
Stop. Don't come any closer.

29
00:02:40,825 --> 00:02:42,945
Why? Or…

30
00:02:43,585 --> 00:02:45,745
-Do you hate our children--
-They're just yours.

31
00:02:46,505 --> 00:02:47,585
I'm not a part of this.

32
00:02:47,665 --> 00:02:49,385
I've never planned to love anyone.

33
00:02:49,465 --> 00:02:51,345
And I never planned to get married.

34
00:02:51,425 --> 00:02:53,905
So there's no way they're mine.

35
00:02:53,985 --> 00:02:55,865
But they are.

36
00:02:55,945 --> 00:02:57,825
Look at their faces.

37
00:02:57,905 --> 00:02:59,105
They look exactly like you.

38
00:02:59,185 --> 00:03:00,985
They're practically your clones.

39
00:03:01,065 --> 00:03:02,665
Stop denying it already.

40
00:03:04,785 --> 00:03:07,265
No. Stop.

41
00:03:07,865 --> 00:03:10,345
No. Stop.

42
00:03:14,305 --> 00:03:15,785
What kind of dream was that?

43
00:03:25,145 --> 00:03:30,665
<i>How long has it been</i>
<i>since I last slept past sunrise?</i>

44
00:03:37,625 --> 00:03:40,465
<i>This is Ruean. And this is Rai.</i>

45
00:03:41,065 --> 00:03:42,225
<i>They're our twins.</i>

46
00:03:43,025 --> 00:03:46,145
That gave me goosebumps.
Why was that dream so vivid?

47
00:05:28,305 --> 00:05:30,985
Song. Hey, you.

48
00:05:31,065 --> 00:05:32,185
Team A is in trouble.

49
00:05:32,265 --> 00:05:35,905
The entire batch of pistachio soup
we made for the OEM client was rejected.

50
00:05:35,985 --> 00:05:38,505
Apparently, the powder
wouldn't dissolve when mixed.

51
00:05:38,585 --> 00:05:40,145
What bad luck.

52
00:05:40,225 --> 00:05:42,305
Damn, Team A. The whole team got hit, huh?

53
00:05:42,385 --> 00:05:44,225
What the hell are they gonna do?

54
00:05:44,305 --> 00:05:45,865
Hey, where are you going?

55
00:05:45,945 --> 00:05:47,025
I'm going to help them.

56
00:05:48,345 --> 00:05:51,185
I'm not letting you go.
It's their team's problem.

57
00:05:51,265 --> 00:05:52,945
Let them deal with it. Sit down.

58
00:05:53,025 --> 00:05:56,305
Nampraw, it doesn't matter
which team it came from.

59
00:05:56,385 --> 00:05:58,385
If we're all from the same
research department,

60
00:05:58,465 --> 00:05:59,865
we have to take responsibility.

61
00:05:59,945 --> 00:06:03,745
Seriously? Again?

62
00:06:04,345 --> 00:06:06,465
The saint of 126 Food.

63
00:06:06,545 --> 00:06:08,945
Give her a crown already.

64
00:06:10,265 --> 00:06:12,705
Do you know what would've happened

65
00:06:12,785 --> 00:06:15,745
if the client hadn't detected it first
and the product got released?

66
00:06:15,825 --> 00:06:17,465
Answer me.

67
00:06:18,265 --> 00:06:19,225
Excuse me.

68
00:06:23,225 --> 00:06:25,025
Can I see the batch record?

69
00:06:25,105 --> 00:06:28,585
(BATCH RECORD: A DOCUMENT SPECIFYING
ALL DETAILS OF THE PRODUCTION PROCESS)

70
00:06:35,345 --> 00:06:39,305
You used the pH value from
the pea protein isolate, right?

71
00:06:40,545 --> 00:06:43,625
These two beans have different structures.

72
00:06:43,705 --> 00:06:45,225
You need to reset the pH value.

73
00:06:45,305 --> 00:06:46,545
Do you still have the sample?

74
00:06:46,625 --> 00:06:48,905
-I'll show you.
-Yes.

75
00:07:31,065 --> 00:07:32,905
It's okay. We can still fix this in time.

76
00:07:36,865 --> 00:07:37,825
What are you doing?

77
00:07:40,785 --> 00:07:42,305
This is my team's issue.

78
00:07:42,385 --> 00:07:45,585
Your team? Then where have you been?

79
00:07:45,665 --> 00:07:47,545
Why weren't you
taking care of your own team?

80
00:07:49,385 --> 00:07:50,625
Who caused the problem?

81
00:07:51,705 --> 00:07:53,505
That person must take the responsibility.

82
00:07:58,905 --> 00:08:00,265
<i>What's so hard about it?</i>

83
00:08:00,345 --> 00:08:03,625
<i>Just do the same thing you did</i>
<i>with the pea-protein.</i>

84
00:08:04,185 --> 00:08:06,145
<i>A bean issue for a pea-brain like you,</i>

85
00:08:06,225 --> 00:08:07,905
<i>you could've handled it.</i>

86
00:08:08,585 --> 00:08:11,545
<i>Stop calling to bother me.</i>
<i>I'm going golfing.</i>

87
00:08:12,985 --> 00:08:17,025
I think you should reconsider
who exactly caused the problem.

88
00:08:17,105 --> 00:08:19,665
-You secretly recorded me?
-That's enough!

89
00:08:27,025 --> 00:08:28,385
The evidence is clear.

90
00:08:28,465 --> 00:08:30,145
You can't deny it anymore, Sarut.

91
00:08:31,985 --> 00:08:33,425
But this time, I'll let it slide

92
00:08:33,505 --> 00:08:36,185
since Song already fixed it.

93
00:08:36,264 --> 00:08:39,385
Besides, I know you've worked
with our company for a long time.

94
00:08:39,465 --> 00:08:42,625
But if something like this happens again,
I won't let you off the hook.

95
00:08:42,705 --> 00:08:45,265
You should think carefully
before doing anything to me, Mudmee.

96
00:08:45,345 --> 00:08:46,865
Did you forget something?

97
00:08:46,945 --> 00:08:49,265
I'm close to the chairwoman.

98
00:08:49,985 --> 00:08:51,425
Your grandmother.

99
00:08:52,905 --> 00:08:54,145
I didn't forget.

100
00:08:54,865 --> 00:08:56,345
But you should know

101
00:08:56,425 --> 00:08:58,505
even if I'm not the company president,

102
00:08:58,585 --> 00:08:59,705
I'm still the CEO.

103
00:09:00,305 --> 00:09:01,785
When the time comes to be ruthless,

104
00:09:01,865 --> 00:09:04,145
I'm not afraid of anyone.

105
00:09:14,945 --> 00:09:16,185
Excuse me.

106
00:09:20,065 --> 00:09:21,705
Thank you so much, Song.

107
00:09:21,785 --> 00:09:23,225
Thank you so much.

108
00:09:23,305 --> 00:09:25,305
-It's okay.
-Excuse me.

109
00:09:26,225 --> 00:09:27,585
Hold on. Wait.

110
00:09:29,625 --> 00:09:32,945
Boss, can I ask you
to transfer her to my team?

111
00:09:38,385 --> 00:09:39,745
Have you asked her yet?

112
00:09:39,825 --> 00:09:41,425
No need to think about it.

113
00:09:43,105 --> 00:09:44,505
I'll go immediately.

114
00:09:50,065 --> 00:09:52,425
You stole the Best Researcher title

115
00:09:52,505 --> 00:09:53,705
from him three years in a row.

116
00:09:53,785 --> 00:09:55,785
And now you even took someone
from his team.

117
00:09:55,865 --> 00:09:57,425
Careful, you're asking for trouble.

118
00:09:57,505 --> 00:09:58,825
Namprow,

119
00:09:58,905 --> 00:10:01,665
the Best Researcher award
is up to the board.

120
00:10:01,745 --> 00:10:04,665
As for Ploy, I just wanted to help her.

121
00:10:04,745 --> 00:10:06,665
If she stayed on that team,
she wouldn't survive.

122
00:10:06,745 --> 00:10:08,265
I'm telling you,

123
00:10:08,345 --> 00:10:10,625
Sarut is definitely
coming back for revenge.

124
00:10:10,705 --> 00:10:12,545
Save up your energy to fight him.

125
00:10:12,625 --> 00:10:15,025
Don't waste it all on

126
00:10:15,105 --> 00:10:17,385
the ladies…

127
00:10:17,465 --> 00:10:19,345
Ooh, they sent a sticker.

128
00:10:20,865 --> 00:10:22,905
Ow, my back cramped up.

129
00:10:22,985 --> 00:10:24,865
Come on, help me first.

130
00:10:30,865 --> 00:10:33,025
<i>I'm ready. You can pick the date.</i>

131
00:10:37,745 --> 00:10:39,145
<i>How about tonight?</i>

132
00:10:40,105 --> 00:10:41,065
<i>Sure thing.</i>

133
00:10:41,825 --> 00:10:45,145
<i>I've picked the date. You pick the place.</i>

134
00:10:46,545 --> 00:10:48,225
<i>How about Saint Che Hotel?</i>

135
00:10:48,305 --> 00:10:50,705
<i>It might be expensive,</i>
<i>but we can split the bill.</i>

136
00:10:51,545 --> 00:10:53,465
I'll take care of that.

137
00:10:53,545 --> 00:10:56,265
Just dress up nicely, like in your photos.

138
00:11:29,025 --> 00:11:30,225
<i>What if she's a catfish</i>

139
00:11:30,305 --> 00:11:32,465
<i>or turns out to be a scammer?</i>
<i>What are you gonna do?</i>

140
00:11:32,545 --> 00:11:33,705
<i>Who in their right mind</i>

141
00:11:33,785 --> 00:11:36,345
<i>uses a cat for a dating app profile?</i>

142
00:11:36,425 --> 00:11:40,025
Come on, if it doesn't work out,
I'll find a way to bail.

143
00:11:40,105 --> 00:11:43,185
We're both women.
She can't do anything to me.

144
00:11:46,105 --> 00:11:48,825
<i>I'm here already. Where are you?</i>

145
00:11:49,785 --> 00:11:53,385
I'M IN THE LOBBY.
BLACK SHIRT, SITTING ALONE.

146
00:12:10,545 --> 00:12:11,465
Excuse me.

147
00:12:13,585 --> 00:12:16,505
Are you the owner of the S2S account?

148
00:12:31,785 --> 00:12:32,705
<i>How can someone</i>

149
00:12:32,785 --> 00:12:35,145
<i>have such a sharp nose that perfectly</i>
<i>matches a beautifully sculpted face?</i>

150
00:12:35,225 --> 00:12:38,225
<i>Her eyes look warm</i>
<i>yet cold at the same time.</i>

151
00:12:38,305 --> 00:12:40,985
<i>Her black hair is smooth like silk.</i>

152
00:12:41,065 --> 00:12:43,665
<i>Damn, even her ears are pretty.</i>

153
00:12:43,745 --> 00:12:47,265
<i>Did God really send</i>
<i>someone this perfect to me?</i>

154
00:12:52,305 --> 00:12:53,865
Why are you staring at me like that?

155
00:12:55,825 --> 00:12:57,465
Or am I not what you expected?

156
00:12:57,545 --> 00:12:59,705
-It's okay if you've changed your mind--
-Uh…

157
00:13:00,305 --> 00:13:01,305
No.

158
00:13:01,945 --> 00:13:04,585
You just look way better than I imagined.

159
00:13:05,385 --> 00:13:06,785
You do too.

160
00:13:09,105 --> 00:13:11,145
And you even…

161
00:13:11,225 --> 00:13:14,025
dressed the way I asked.

162
00:13:15,305 --> 00:13:16,385
So…

163
00:13:17,105 --> 00:13:18,265
do you like it?

164
00:13:18,865 --> 00:13:19,945
I do.

165
00:13:23,025 --> 00:13:24,145
Very much.

166
00:13:30,305 --> 00:13:32,985
Here's my test results.

167
00:13:33,585 --> 00:13:34,825
Here's mine.

168
00:13:37,105 --> 00:13:38,785
MEDICAL EXAMINATION REPORT

169
00:13:45,825 --> 00:13:48,185
Should we head upstairs, then?

170
00:13:48,265 --> 00:13:49,505
So we don't waste time.

171
00:13:51,305 --> 00:13:52,185
Okay.

172
00:14:14,105 --> 00:14:15,665
Wait.

173
00:14:15,745 --> 00:14:19,665
We don't even know each other's names yet.

174
00:14:19,745 --> 00:14:21,425
There's no need to know.

175
00:14:22,345 --> 00:14:24,345
Don't you remember our deal?

176
00:14:24,945 --> 00:14:26,465
I do.

177
00:14:26,545 --> 00:14:30,425
Our deal is just for tonight.

178
00:14:31,825 --> 00:14:35,865
Then we separate, with no contact.

179
00:14:35,945 --> 00:14:40,025
Never see each other again.
It's okay if you don't want to tell me.

180
00:14:40,105 --> 00:14:44,105
But I want you to know, my name is Piang.

181
00:14:44,625 --> 00:14:48,025
Okay. Is there anything else
you want to tell me?

182
00:14:48,105 --> 00:14:50,985
If not, I'll continue.

183
00:15:17,345 --> 00:15:18,865
Your heart is beating so fast.

184
00:15:20,105 --> 00:15:21,425
Can you take it?

185
00:15:22,545 --> 00:15:23,705
I can.

186
00:15:26,065 --> 00:15:27,425
Then…

187
00:15:28,465 --> 00:15:30,425
hold on until I'm satisfied.

188
00:15:46,465 --> 00:15:48,505
-Get some water.
-Water.

189
00:15:48,585 --> 00:15:49,545
Here, water.

190
00:15:51,145 --> 00:15:54,105
Alright, everyone. We've now reached

191
00:15:54,185 --> 00:15:57,265
the final set of the championship match.

192
00:15:57,345 --> 00:15:59,745
Alright, please welcome the athletes

193
00:15:59,825 --> 00:16:02,385
from both teams to take their positions.

194
00:16:44,905 --> 00:16:46,265
You're here already?

195
00:16:46,345 --> 00:16:48,385
Come in.
I'm at the far end of the bleachers.

196
00:16:55,185 --> 00:16:56,745
I'm here.

197
00:16:58,705 --> 00:17:02,145
Go, Song, go!

198
00:17:03,145 --> 00:17:04,505
Why are you pouting like that?

199
00:17:04,585 --> 00:17:07,585
Because of you.
I don't even know why you made me come.

200
00:17:07,665 --> 00:17:09,785
You know I'm not into sports.

201
00:17:09,865 --> 00:17:12,424
Come on, it's the company's annual event.

202
00:17:12,505 --> 00:17:14,505
Let people see your face once in a while.

203
00:17:14,585 --> 00:17:16,545
You're one of the owners here.

204
00:17:17,905 --> 00:17:19,305
So boring.

205
00:17:31,625 --> 00:17:32,625
That's…

206
00:17:36,425 --> 00:17:37,505
Her name is Song.

207
00:17:37,585 --> 00:17:38,825
Sadanun Warakij.

208
00:17:38,905 --> 00:17:41,305
She's one of the company's
top food researchers.

209
00:17:43,425 --> 00:17:44,585
<i>Holy crap.</i>

210
00:17:44,665 --> 00:17:47,425
<i>S2S works at my company?</i>

211
00:17:47,505 --> 00:17:49,745
<i>Could we actually be soulmates?</i>

212
00:17:50,385 --> 00:17:51,425
<i>That's why we met again.</i>

213
00:17:52,305 --> 00:17:53,545
<i>Alright, Piang.</i>

214
00:17:53,625 --> 00:17:55,945
<i>I can't let her slip away</i>
<i>so easily this time.</i>

215
00:18:04,705 --> 00:18:06,905
Namprow, who's that?

216
00:18:06,985 --> 00:18:08,265
The one next to the boss.

217
00:18:08,345 --> 00:18:09,865
Ah, that's Piang.

218
00:18:09,945 --> 00:18:12,025
The chairwoman's youngest granddaughter.

219
00:18:12,625 --> 00:18:13,865
I've never seen her before.

220
00:18:13,945 --> 00:18:16,025
Well, she doesn't hold any position
in the company.

221
00:18:16,105 --> 00:18:19,625
She's just the heir apparent, get it?
She only shows up once in a while.

222
00:18:19,705 --> 00:18:22,225
Why? Does the chairwoman
love her grandkids differently?

223
00:18:22,305 --> 00:18:23,785
One's the CEO,

224
00:18:23,865 --> 00:18:26,585
while the other has no position at all.

225
00:18:26,665 --> 00:18:29,825
Listen. The chairwoman
did prepare a position for her.

226
00:18:29,905 --> 00:18:31,065
Apparently, she didn't like it.

227
00:18:31,145 --> 00:18:34,145
I heard she's actually
super self-indulgent.

228
00:18:34,745 --> 00:18:35,865
She's pretty, though.

229
00:18:42,145 --> 00:18:45,825
And this year's badminton champion is…

230
00:18:45,905 --> 00:18:49,785
Sadanun, from Team B
of the Research Department.

231
00:18:56,425 --> 00:18:57,625
You're amazing.

232
00:18:58,385 --> 00:19:00,145
She's so good.

233
00:19:14,705 --> 00:19:16,745
Her abs are incredible.

234
00:19:16,825 --> 00:19:17,825
What did you say?

235
00:19:19,345 --> 00:19:23,625
Nothing. I was just saying
she's really good.

236
00:19:24,585 --> 00:19:25,865
I had no idea

237
00:19:25,945 --> 00:19:29,345
our company had someone
this beautiful and talented.

238
00:19:30,345 --> 00:19:31,745
She's not only good at sports.

239
00:19:31,825 --> 00:19:34,905
She's also won Best Researcher
three years in a row.

240
00:19:34,985 --> 00:19:36,985
Even though she's only been here
for five years.

241
00:19:37,065 --> 00:19:38,425
She's so good at everything

242
00:19:38,505 --> 00:19:40,545
even some senior researchers get jealous.

243
00:19:45,585 --> 00:19:47,385
Stay here, I'll go present the award.

244
00:19:47,465 --> 00:19:48,785
Uh, Mud,

245
00:19:50,505 --> 00:19:51,985
can I present the award instead?

246
00:19:52,745 --> 00:19:55,985
Please? Please?

247
00:19:56,065 --> 00:19:59,305
You wanted everyone to remember me, right?

248
00:19:59,385 --> 00:20:01,825
Well, now everyone in the stadium
can see me clearly.

249
00:20:01,905 --> 00:20:03,345
Let's make it a grand opening.

250
00:20:05,185 --> 00:20:06,385
Please?

251
00:20:09,065 --> 00:20:10,385
Okay.

252
00:20:10,465 --> 00:20:14,025
Alright, now it's time for
the award presentation ceremony.

253
00:20:14,105 --> 00:20:16,305
I'd like to invite Miss Mud…

254
00:20:19,705 --> 00:20:22,505
Ah, please welcome Miss Piang,

255
00:20:22,585 --> 00:20:24,505
Piangrawin Chatpimuk,

256
00:20:24,585 --> 00:20:26,745
the chairwoman's youngest granddaughter.

257
00:20:26,825 --> 00:20:29,945
She's also one of the company's
important figures.

258
00:20:30,025 --> 00:20:33,625
Please come present the award
to the athlete.

259
00:20:37,985 --> 00:20:39,945
Congratulations.

260
00:20:42,065 --> 00:20:43,785
-<i>What?</i>
-Congratulations.

261
00:20:43,865 --> 00:20:46,665
<i>She's the chairwoman's</i>
<i>youngest granddaughter?</i>

262
00:21:06,785 --> 00:21:08,305
Why are you avoiding me?

263
00:21:08,385 --> 00:21:10,065
Look at me.

264
00:21:10,905 --> 00:21:13,905
Nice to see you again, Song.

265
00:21:33,625 --> 00:21:34,705
Song.

266
00:21:34,785 --> 00:21:37,665
<i>Song…</i>

267
00:21:44,985 --> 00:21:48,025
You did so good! Bravo!

268
00:22:00,385 --> 00:22:01,865
Hey…

269
00:22:03,865 --> 00:22:07,225
I don't think I can handle this.

270
00:22:07,305 --> 00:22:09,425
But I haven't even done anything yet.

271
00:22:10,185 --> 00:22:11,785
Toughen up.

272
00:22:28,865 --> 00:22:30,065
Are you hurt?

273
00:22:31,745 --> 00:22:33,025
Actually,

274
00:22:33,865 --> 00:22:35,985
this is my first time.

275
00:22:37,865 --> 00:22:39,705
Why did you let me do this?

276
00:22:41,745 --> 00:22:43,145
I don't know.

277
00:22:45,025 --> 00:22:47,865
Even though we're strangers,

278
00:22:48,385 --> 00:22:52,945
I feel like
there's something connecting us.

279
00:22:53,545 --> 00:22:57,225
And I don't regret it.

280
00:22:58,265 --> 00:23:00,225
Not even a little.

281
00:23:01,265 --> 00:23:02,665
Are you sure?

282
00:23:05,585 --> 00:23:07,185
I'm sure.

283
00:23:08,745 --> 00:23:10,105
Then…

284
00:23:11,505 --> 00:23:13,425
I'll take it slow, okay?

285
00:23:39,345 --> 00:23:40,665
Don't spill it.

286
00:24:20,665 --> 00:24:22,545
Does it still hurt?

287
00:24:26,745 --> 00:24:27,865
A little.

288
00:24:29,225 --> 00:24:30,745
But I like it.

289
00:24:40,825 --> 00:24:41,865
Hey…

290
00:24:42,625 --> 00:24:46,345
after tonight, can we meet again?

291
00:24:46,425 --> 00:24:47,545
Please?

292
00:24:50,425 --> 00:24:53,945
I know we already made an agreement,

293
00:24:54,025 --> 00:24:56,545
but I really can't stop myself.

294
00:24:56,625 --> 00:24:57,785
I like you.

295
00:24:59,505 --> 00:25:00,705
Please go. I'm not in the mood.

296
00:25:01,345 --> 00:25:02,465
Wait.

297
00:25:03,145 --> 00:25:04,665
I'm sorry.

298
00:25:04,745 --> 00:25:07,065
I just wanted to see you again.

299
00:25:07,145 --> 00:25:11,025
I already told you
I don't want a serious relationship.

300
00:25:11,105 --> 00:25:12,465
If you're thinking that far ahead,

301
00:25:12,545 --> 00:25:14,185
then this is where we end.

302
00:25:19,225 --> 00:25:21,025
I'm sorry.

303
00:25:21,105 --> 00:25:24,385
Wait, please. Listen to me first.

304
00:25:24,985 --> 00:25:26,265
Hey.

305
00:25:33,305 --> 00:25:36,265
God. Why am I so damn unlucky?

306
00:25:40,185 --> 00:25:41,705
This is so damn annoying.

307
00:25:44,505 --> 00:25:46,105
<i>You're done competing, right?</i>

308
00:25:46,185 --> 00:25:48,905
<i>Do you still have enough energy</i>
<i>to drink with me?</i>

309
00:25:49,585 --> 00:25:52,705
Sure. I'm already losing my mind anyway.

310
00:25:52,785 --> 00:25:54,745
I seriously need alcohol therapy.

311
00:26:50,225 --> 00:26:51,385
You started without me.

312
00:26:52,265 --> 00:26:53,505
Don't be mad.

313
00:26:53,585 --> 00:26:56,025
Come on, tell me.
What's stressing you out today?

314
00:26:56,105 --> 00:26:58,225
Not yet. I don't want to talk about it.

315
00:26:58,865 --> 00:27:00,105
Then don't talk about it yet.

316
00:27:01,305 --> 00:27:02,705
Let's drink and go dance.

317
00:27:03,345 --> 00:27:06,825
I'm gonna make you forget everything.

318
00:27:06,905 --> 00:27:08,065
Sounds good.

319
00:27:43,705 --> 00:27:44,865
<i>You didn't want anything serious</i>

320
00:27:44,945 --> 00:27:46,905
<i>because you already</i>
<i>have your own milk cow, huh?</i>

321
00:28:26,225 --> 00:28:27,425
Whoa.

322
00:28:27,505 --> 00:28:29,265
Are you cooking today, Grandma?

323
00:28:29,345 --> 00:28:30,305
Of course.

324
00:28:30,385 --> 00:28:35,265
This morning, I woke up early
to make breakfast especially for you.

325
00:28:36,705 --> 00:28:38,545
What's the special occasion?

326
00:28:38,625 --> 00:28:39,745
Oh, it's nothing.

327
00:28:40,345 --> 00:28:44,145
It's just that I noticed you
woke up later than usual today.

328
00:28:44,225 --> 00:28:47,625
So I figured you probably
don't have sleeping problems anymore.

329
00:28:47,705 --> 00:28:50,585
More importantly, you haven't dreamed
about Neung again, right?

330
00:28:52,305 --> 00:28:56,745
Right. Ever since I had that weird dream…

331
00:28:57,345 --> 00:29:00,465
A weird dream?
What did you dream about, sweetheart?

332
00:29:01,425 --> 00:29:03,825
I dreamed about a woman.

333
00:29:03,905 --> 00:29:07,865
She was carrying twin babies,
and she said they were our children.

334
00:29:08,545 --> 00:29:10,585
After that,
I never dreamed about Neung again.

335
00:29:15,465 --> 00:29:19,465
Maybe you've finally met your soulmate.

336
00:29:20,625 --> 00:29:21,785
Grandma.

337
00:29:21,865 --> 00:29:23,665
What soulmate?

338
00:29:23,745 --> 00:29:25,825
I can't even remember her face.

339
00:29:25,905 --> 00:29:29,065
Besides, you know I don't want anyone.

340
00:29:29,145 --> 00:29:31,825
I'm perfectly happy
staying single like this.

341
00:29:31,905 --> 00:29:33,705
So I can take care of you forever.

342
00:29:36,305 --> 00:29:38,505
You don't need to say things like that.

343
00:29:38,585 --> 00:29:41,505
Because this Grandma is strong.

344
00:29:41,585 --> 00:29:43,425
I can take care of myself.

345
00:29:44,025 --> 00:29:47,065
Honestly, I've secretly noticed

346
00:29:47,145 --> 00:29:49,665
that you keep swiping right,

347
00:29:49,745 --> 00:29:52,185
swiping right all the time.

348
00:29:52,265 --> 00:29:54,745
You've been secretly
going on dates, haven't you?

349
00:29:54,825 --> 00:29:56,585
Seriously,

350
00:29:56,665 --> 00:29:58,945
with all that swiping right,

351
00:29:59,025 --> 00:30:01,585
haven't you found anyone special yet?

352
00:30:03,105 --> 00:30:04,985
<i>Nice to see you again,</i>

353
00:30:07,585 --> 00:30:08,745
Song.

354
00:30:11,865 --> 00:30:14,385
Nope. No one at all.

355
00:30:15,545 --> 00:30:17,745
Song, listen to me.

356
00:30:17,825 --> 00:30:20,425
I don't want you

357
00:30:20,505 --> 00:30:23,545
to shut yourself off too much, okay?

358
00:30:23,625 --> 00:30:26,265
Because I believe that someone like you,

359
00:30:26,345 --> 00:30:29,745
will definitely meet someone good one day.

360
00:30:29,825 --> 00:30:31,345
Someone who's ready to love you,

361
00:30:31,425 --> 00:30:35,505
and who'll never hurt you like before.

362
00:30:35,585 --> 00:30:40,185
And I believe that Neung
would want that too.

363
00:30:43,385 --> 00:30:44,905
Well, anyway,

364
00:30:45,545 --> 00:30:48,105
we only have each other now.

365
00:30:48,185 --> 00:30:51,505
Whatever makes you uncomfortable,

366
00:30:51,585 --> 00:30:54,105
Grandma won't force you.

367
00:30:55,505 --> 00:30:59,385
That's exactly why I love you so much

368
00:31:00,025 --> 00:31:02,025
and never want to leave you.

369
00:31:03,145 --> 00:31:05,865
You're such a sweet talker.

370
00:31:05,945 --> 00:31:07,025
Let me kiss your cheek.

371
00:31:09,905 --> 00:31:11,505
That feels refreshing.

372
00:31:11,585 --> 00:31:13,105
Alright, here you go.

373
00:31:13,185 --> 00:31:15,145
-Ready?
-Ready.

374
00:31:15,225 --> 00:31:19,985
I remember that you like lots of pepper.

375
00:31:27,145 --> 00:31:28,905
Maybe that's not her girlfriend.

376
00:31:28,985 --> 00:31:32,025
Maybe she's just another
dating app match, like me.

377
00:31:32,105 --> 00:31:33,425
But no…

378
00:31:33,505 --> 00:31:36,465
they looked closer than that.

379
00:31:38,785 --> 00:31:40,065
I'm annoyed.

380
00:31:53,825 --> 00:31:55,625
What are you whining about, Piang?

381
00:31:55,705 --> 00:31:57,585
You're up earlier than usual too.

382
00:31:59,185 --> 00:32:00,865
I haven't slept at all.

383
00:32:00,945 --> 00:32:02,785
I kept thinking about your researcher.

384
00:32:07,225 --> 00:32:10,105
Mud, is Song single?

385
00:32:15,785 --> 00:32:16,745
I don't know.

386
00:32:16,825 --> 00:32:18,865
Usually, I only see her at work.

387
00:32:18,945 --> 00:32:21,065
Not many people know much
about her personal life.

388
00:32:21,145 --> 00:32:22,305
True.

389
00:32:22,385 --> 00:32:25,025
Even her IG and Facebook
are set to private.

390
00:32:25,625 --> 00:32:27,665
So how am I supposed to find out?

391
00:32:31,025 --> 00:32:32,145
Find out what?

392
00:32:32,225 --> 00:32:33,385
Don't tell me

393
00:32:33,465 --> 00:32:36,345
you've become this obsessed with her
after meeting just once.

394
00:32:36,425 --> 00:32:38,185
It wasn't just once.

395
00:32:38,265 --> 00:32:40,385
We know each other better than that.

396
00:32:40,465 --> 00:32:43,745
Song and I matched on a dating app.

397
00:32:43,825 --> 00:32:46,665
And… we slept together.

398
00:32:46,745 --> 00:32:47,745
What?

399
00:32:49,785 --> 00:32:50,985
-Hey.
-What?

400
00:32:51,065 --> 00:32:52,665
Do you even realize what you've done?

401
00:32:52,745 --> 00:32:54,025
I do.

402
00:32:54,105 --> 00:32:57,065
Maybe we started in a way
other people wouldn't approve of,

403
00:32:57,145 --> 00:32:58,465
but I really do like her.

404
00:32:58,545 --> 00:33:01,105
I've thought about her every day
since that night we parted.

405
00:33:01,185 --> 00:33:03,425
And I kept asking myself
how I could see her again.

406
00:33:03,505 --> 00:33:06,145
And then, you two met again.

407
00:33:06,225 --> 00:33:07,465
By coincidence?

408
00:33:10,345 --> 00:33:12,065
If Grandma finds out, you're dead.

409
00:33:13,425 --> 00:33:17,185
I won't die. I've already graduated
and fulfilled my promise.

410
00:33:17,265 --> 00:33:19,865
-I can do whatever I want.
-No.

411
00:33:19,945 --> 00:33:21,265
What if she cuts off your credit cards?

412
00:33:25,825 --> 00:33:27,105
Then what should I do?

413
00:33:27,185 --> 00:33:28,745
I don't want to give up so easily.

414
00:33:29,345 --> 00:33:30,505
I've lived for 24 years,

415
00:33:30,585 --> 00:33:32,905
and no one has ever made
my heart race like this before.

416
00:33:33,985 --> 00:33:36,505
I think this has to be fate between us.

417
00:33:43,505 --> 00:33:44,545
How about this?

418
00:33:46,425 --> 00:33:49,025
Keep this a secret for now.

419
00:33:49,705 --> 00:33:52,145
Don't let Grandma find out. Got it?

420
00:33:53,865 --> 00:33:56,305
And if you need any help, just tell me.

421
00:33:56,905 --> 00:33:59,465
You're the sweetest.

422
00:34:26,145 --> 00:34:27,824
Stop hibernating already, Grandma.

423
00:34:29,025 --> 00:34:31,225
It's rare for us
to have breakfast together.

424
00:34:33,585 --> 00:34:36,744
True. What got into you
to wake up at this hour?

425
00:34:37,344 --> 00:34:38,705
Normally,

426
00:34:38,784 --> 00:34:43,304
I only see you buried in bed
until the afternoon, don't I?

427
00:34:43,385 --> 00:34:45,625
I'm going to the company with Mud.

428
00:34:45,705 --> 00:34:47,264
But I'm not going there to work.

429
00:34:47,344 --> 00:34:48,585
I'm going to follow my heart.

430
00:34:49,705 --> 00:34:51,264
What are you talking about, Piang?

431
00:34:53,385 --> 00:34:55,784
She's just talking nonsense, Grandma.

432
00:34:55,865 --> 00:34:58,985
She probably wants
to observe things at the company.

433
00:34:59,065 --> 00:35:01,505
If she finds something she likes,
she can try doing it.

434
00:35:01,585 --> 00:35:04,105
She doesn't want to keep
being a burden to you.

435
00:35:05,905 --> 00:35:07,385
It's good that you think that way.

436
00:35:07,465 --> 00:35:09,905
But honestly,

437
00:35:09,985 --> 00:35:12,025
I don't think you're suited
for any kind of work.

438
00:35:12,945 --> 00:35:15,625
That's why I never expected
anything from you regarding the company.

439
00:35:15,705 --> 00:35:17,665
What I want

440
00:35:17,745 --> 00:35:21,985
is for you to find someone,
start a family, get married,

441
00:35:22,065 --> 00:35:23,785
and give me great-grandchildren.

442
00:35:23,865 --> 00:35:26,185
You've graduated already. It's about time.

443
00:35:26,825 --> 00:35:28,625
Why does it have to be me?

444
00:35:28,705 --> 00:35:31,385
You never pressure Pi Mud to get married.

445
00:35:31,465 --> 00:35:34,865
That's because Mudmee is capable,
and she doesn't need anyone.

446
00:35:34,945 --> 00:35:38,185
One day, she'll take over
as company president after me.

447
00:35:38,265 --> 00:35:41,145
She doesn't have time
to care about romance.

448
00:35:41,225 --> 00:35:44,305
But Grandma, everyone wants love.

449
00:35:44,385 --> 00:35:45,625
Don't use your own way of thinking

450
00:35:45,705 --> 00:35:47,905
to judge other people like this.

451
00:35:47,985 --> 00:35:49,745
Didn't you say you didn't want to get old?

452
00:35:49,825 --> 00:35:51,225
Hey, Piang.

453
00:35:52,145 --> 00:35:54,425
I'm full already. I'll wait in the car.

454
00:35:58,025 --> 00:36:00,425
Listen. Remember this.

455
00:36:00,505 --> 00:36:02,585
No matter who Piang falls for or likes,

456
00:36:02,665 --> 00:36:07,185
I will never allow someone
with no background into this house.

457
00:36:07,265 --> 00:36:08,665
As her older sister,

458
00:36:08,745 --> 00:36:11,585
you have to keep an eye on her for me.
Understand?

459
00:36:13,265 --> 00:36:14,425
Yes, Grandma.

460
00:36:31,665 --> 00:36:34,545
I need to go take care of some work first,
but I'll be back soon.

461
00:36:34,625 --> 00:36:37,105
Don't do anything too outrageous.

462
00:36:37,185 --> 00:36:38,625
Grandma has a lot of eyes here.

463
00:36:40,065 --> 00:36:42,505
Understood. But no promises.

464
00:36:42,585 --> 00:36:45,945
Piang.

465
00:36:48,745 --> 00:36:50,025
Damn it.

466
00:36:52,865 --> 00:36:54,185
Ready?

467
00:37:06,185 --> 00:37:09,185
Oh, Ploy, help me run this lab test.

468
00:37:09,265 --> 00:37:10,705
I want to know

469
00:37:10,785 --> 00:37:13,985
roughly how much protein
and healthy fats are in fish.

470
00:37:14,065 --> 00:37:15,185
Sure.

471
00:37:16,625 --> 00:37:17,905
Hello, everyone.

472
00:37:23,585 --> 00:37:25,585
Piang, what are you doing here?

473
00:37:26,505 --> 00:37:31,185
I came looking for someone
who stole my heart.

474
00:37:38,505 --> 00:37:40,385
I'm kidding, it's nothing.

475
00:37:40,465 --> 00:37:41,865
Oh, okay.

476
00:37:54,025 --> 00:37:55,705
-What now?
-What now?

477
00:37:55,785 --> 00:37:58,265
Hey, you. Who said you could sit there?

478
00:37:59,145 --> 00:38:00,225
No one.

479
00:38:00,305 --> 00:38:02,665
But this is my grandmother's company,

480
00:38:02,745 --> 00:38:04,985
and this chair belongs to my family too.

481
00:38:05,065 --> 00:38:06,745
I can sit whenever I want.

482
00:38:06,825 --> 00:38:08,945
I don't need anyone's permission.

483
00:38:09,945 --> 00:38:10,865
Nampraw.

484
00:38:10,945 --> 00:38:12,225
Uh, yes?

485
00:38:14,825 --> 00:38:18,345
Piang, Song doesn't like
being disturbed while working.

486
00:38:18,425 --> 00:38:20,985
Why don't you wait in the lounge for now?

487
00:38:21,065 --> 00:38:22,505
The air conditioning is nice and cool.

488
00:38:22,585 --> 00:38:24,145
-You're very welcome there.
-No.

489
00:38:24,225 --> 00:38:25,945
I'll stay here.

490
00:38:26,025 --> 00:38:27,545
Oh, okay.

491
00:38:28,505 --> 00:38:30,585
So, are you working on a new project?

492
00:38:30,665 --> 00:38:31,945
Yes, Piang.

493
00:38:32,025 --> 00:38:33,985
We're developing a new product right now.

494
00:38:34,065 --> 00:38:36,625
It's a health product made from fish meat.

495
00:38:36,705 --> 00:38:38,865
Our demo is almost finished now.

496
00:38:38,945 --> 00:38:41,545
If you're free someday,
you can come try it.

497
00:38:41,625 --> 00:38:43,225
I'll prepare everything for you.

498
00:38:46,145 --> 00:38:47,305
Your name is Ploy?

499
00:38:47,385 --> 00:38:49,545
We're probably around the same age.

500
00:38:49,625 --> 00:38:51,585
Nice to meet you.

501
00:38:53,425 --> 00:38:54,905
My hands are dirty, Piang.

502
00:38:55,705 --> 00:38:57,625
It's okay, I don't mind.

503
00:39:05,505 --> 00:39:06,705
You should go now.

504
00:39:06,785 --> 00:39:08,785
Don't make me say it twice.

505
00:39:13,825 --> 00:39:15,505
I'll go then.

506
00:39:23,865 --> 00:39:25,345
Oh my.

507
00:39:25,945 --> 00:39:27,745
Work hard, okay?

508
00:39:40,825 --> 00:39:42,305
-What was that about?
-No idea.

509
00:39:43,985 --> 00:39:45,425
She's blushing.

510
00:39:45,505 --> 00:39:48,185
This is the face of someone in love.

511
00:39:48,265 --> 00:39:49,625
-Just teasing.
-She doesn't like it.

512
00:39:54,985 --> 00:39:56,345
Hello.

513
00:39:58,065 --> 00:40:00,785
One hot americano, please.

514
00:40:00,865 --> 00:40:01,985
Sure.

515
00:40:03,985 --> 00:40:05,785
-It's all set.
-Please wait a moment.

516
00:40:05,865 --> 00:40:06,945
Sure.

517
00:40:28,425 --> 00:40:31,785
<i>Mudmee is capable,</i>
<i>and she doesn't need anyone.</i>

518
00:40:31,865 --> 00:40:35,305
Soon, she'll be taking over
as company president after me.

519
00:40:35,385 --> 00:40:38,385
She doesn't have time
to care about love or relationships.

520
00:40:41,025 --> 00:40:42,865
Your hot americano is ready.

521
00:40:43,905 --> 00:40:44,945
Thank you.

522
00:41:12,945 --> 00:41:15,345
I'm sorry. I didn't mean to.

523
00:41:16,185 --> 00:41:17,425
I understand.

524
00:41:17,505 --> 00:41:21,865
But I'm on my way to a job interview,
and it's almost time already.

525
00:41:24,145 --> 00:41:25,425
I'm sorry.

526
00:41:29,585 --> 00:41:31,625
Then could you wait a moment?

527
00:41:32,225 --> 00:41:33,545
I'll take care of it.

528
00:41:48,545 --> 00:41:49,705
Boss.

529
00:41:49,785 --> 00:41:51,505
-I got it for you.
-Thank you.

530
00:41:52,625 --> 00:41:53,585
Here.

531
00:41:55,065 --> 00:41:56,265
It's for you.

532
00:41:56,345 --> 00:41:59,345
Your clothes are stained like this.
How will you go to the interview?

533
00:42:02,025 --> 00:42:03,305
This is too much.

534
00:42:03,385 --> 00:42:05,025
But for a job interview,

535
00:42:05,105 --> 00:42:07,225
first impressions are important,
aren't they?

536
00:42:07,945 --> 00:42:08,905
Please keep it.

537
00:42:22,985 --> 00:42:24,105
Thank you.

538
00:42:33,065 --> 00:42:36,305
Once I'm done, I'll wash it
and return it to you right away.

539
00:42:38,025 --> 00:42:39,585
That's okay.

540
00:42:40,705 --> 00:42:42,385
You can keep this outfit.

541
00:42:42,465 --> 00:42:44,105
Consider it my apology.

542
00:42:44,185 --> 00:42:46,585
I can't do that, it's too expensive.

543
00:42:46,665 --> 00:42:47,905
I can't accept it.

544
00:42:47,985 --> 00:42:50,265
May I have your business card?

545
00:42:50,345 --> 00:42:52,745
Once I'm done,
I'll send it back to the address.

546
00:43:00,225 --> 00:43:01,505
Here you go.

547
00:43:01,585 --> 00:43:02,585
Thank you.

548
00:43:03,985 --> 00:43:05,065
Oh, hey.

549
00:43:07,425 --> 00:43:08,665
Good luck.

550
00:43:08,745 --> 00:43:09,865
Thank you.

551
00:43:44,105 --> 00:43:48,465
Ploy. Ploy.

552
00:43:49,425 --> 00:43:51,225
Ploy. Ploy.

553
00:43:52,025 --> 00:43:52,865
Piang.

554
00:43:53,945 --> 00:43:55,225
Are you okay?

555
00:43:55,305 --> 00:43:57,105
Can I have a moment?

556
00:44:00,105 --> 00:44:02,905
-Song has a girlfriend?
-Yes.

557
00:44:02,985 --> 00:44:06,305
I've been pursuing her,
but she's not interested.

558
00:44:06,385 --> 00:44:09,745
So I started wondering
if maybe she already has a girlfriend.

559
00:44:14,705 --> 00:44:15,745
This woman here.

560
00:44:22,505 --> 00:44:24,425
I'm not really sure either, Piang.

561
00:44:24,505 --> 00:44:26,825
I just transferred to Song's team.

562
00:44:27,425 --> 00:44:29,545
If I suddenly ask about this,

563
00:44:29,625 --> 00:44:31,425
it might seem a little nosy.

564
00:44:33,825 --> 00:44:34,945
True.

565
00:44:39,825 --> 00:44:40,865
But don't worry.

566
00:44:40,945 --> 00:44:43,465
I will handle it for you.

567
00:44:43,545 --> 00:44:44,505
Really?

568
00:44:45,385 --> 00:44:46,785
Thank you, Ploy.

569
00:44:48,305 --> 00:44:49,465
You're welcome.

570
00:45:07,945 --> 00:45:09,305
POST

571
00:45:22,105 --> 00:45:25,585
NEUNG MUST BE SO PROUD

572
00:45:39,785 --> 00:45:41,225
A model?

573
00:45:53,425 --> 00:45:56,345
<i>It's a long night ahead. Care to join me?</i>

574
00:47:50,905 --> 00:47:54,305
With all that staring,
why not just come over?

575
00:47:54,385 --> 00:47:57,105
Why do I have to make the first move?

576
00:47:58,185 --> 00:48:00,825
I just wanted to double-check
that you came alone

577
00:48:02,025 --> 00:48:03,225
and not with anyone else.

578
00:48:04,145 --> 00:48:07,105
Who exactly are you referring to?

579
00:48:10,745 --> 00:48:12,105
Your girlfriend, of course.

580
00:48:13,505 --> 00:48:14,985
I'm single.

581
00:48:16,225 --> 00:48:17,585
And I'll probably stay single

582
00:48:19,025 --> 00:48:20,385
for the rest of my life.

583
00:48:49,025 --> 00:48:50,825
<i>The way is clear.</i>

584
00:48:50,905 --> 00:48:52,785
<i>Those two aren't dating.</i>

585
00:49:25,545 --> 00:49:28,225
What? I thought Ploy was going
to prepare the tasting for me.

586
00:49:29,025 --> 00:49:30,905
How did it end up being you?

587
00:49:30,985 --> 00:49:33,145
She suddenly had to run to the bathroom,

588
00:49:33,785 --> 00:49:35,625
so she asked me to do it instead.

589
00:49:36,225 --> 00:49:38,225
Quite a coincidence, don't you think?

590
00:49:42,265 --> 00:49:45,985
I think… it's fate instead.

591
00:49:55,465 --> 00:49:57,505
Here. Hurry up and taste it.

592
00:49:57,585 --> 00:49:59,105
I still have work to do.

593
00:50:11,225 --> 00:50:12,145
It's really delicious.

594
00:50:13,465 --> 00:50:16,465
I wonder if it's the recipe
or the person who made it?

595
00:50:18,665 --> 00:50:20,745
By the way, what kind of fish is this?

596
00:50:20,825 --> 00:50:22,185
It's suckerfish.

597
00:50:25,505 --> 00:50:26,785
Are you calling me a leech?

598
00:50:26,865 --> 00:50:28,785
Well, you're acting exactly like one.

599
00:50:28,865 --> 00:50:29,985
You won't let go.

600
00:50:30,585 --> 00:50:32,745
I'm just following my heart.

601
00:50:32,825 --> 00:50:34,145
I like you.

602
00:50:34,225 --> 00:50:37,225
And I'm pretty sure
you feel something for me too.

603
00:50:38,065 --> 00:50:39,665
You really love making things up.

604
00:50:39,745 --> 00:50:42,305
Yes, I'm very good at it.

605
00:50:42,385 --> 00:50:44,705
So good that
I can already picture our future.

606
00:50:44,785 --> 00:50:47,385
We'll get married
and have twin babies together.

607
00:50:47,465 --> 00:50:49,225
Their names will be Ruean and Rai.

608
00:50:49,305 --> 00:50:52,985
<i>Their names will be Ruean and Rai.</i>

609
00:50:53,065 --> 00:50:54,025
<i>This is Ruean.</i>

610
00:50:54,705 --> 00:50:56,305
<i>And this is Rai.</i>

611
00:50:56,385 --> 00:50:57,905
<i>They're our twins.</i>

612
00:51:07,545 --> 00:51:08,585
Song.

613
00:51:10,305 --> 00:51:13,985
<i>This girl is the one who confessed</i>
<i>to me after we slept together.</i>

614
00:51:14,065 --> 00:51:16,625
<i>She's also the one</i>
<i>I tried to stay away from.</i>

615
00:51:16,705 --> 00:51:18,705
<i>But she's also the one</i>
<i>who appears in my dreams,</i>

616
00:51:18,785 --> 00:51:20,985
<i>and stopped giving me nightmares.</i>

617
00:51:21,065 --> 00:51:22,945
<i>What kind of crazy mess is this?</i>

618
00:52:02,665 --> 00:52:04,865
<i>I want to open a matcha café.</i>

619
00:52:04,945 --> 00:52:05,985
<i>I want to build something of my own.</i>

620
00:52:06,065 --> 00:52:08,065
<i>I want to become</i>
<i>the kind of person you like.</i>

621
00:52:08,145 --> 00:52:10,105
<i>You're Matika, right?</i>

622
00:52:10,185 --> 00:52:12,145
<i>Yes, Kwanrin.</i>

623
00:52:13,665 --> 00:52:15,545
<i>Ple, can you help me with something?</i>

624
00:52:15,625 --> 00:52:17,505
<i>Make that woman heartbroken.</i>

625
00:52:19,905 --> 00:52:21,705
<i>Piang, don't overthink it.</i>

626
00:52:21,785 --> 00:52:24,665
<i>I think Song</i>
<i>was probably just teasing you.</i>

627
00:52:24,745 --> 00:52:26,265
Piang.

